Omninuera AI - Intern Offer Letter (Draft) — Legal Review
=======================================================

Legal summary (primary concerns & required clarifications)
- Primary legal concerns: (1) Strengthen IP assignment language and execution mechanics to ensure enforceability under Indian law; (2) Clarify stipend classification to reduce misclassification risk and state tax/TDS and social security (PF/ESI) consequences; (3) Confirm whether the internship falls under the Apprentices Act or is academic/short-term training — this affects registration and statutory obligations.
- Required clarifications for HR: Is this internship (a) part of an academic course (credit-bearing), (b) a bona fide training program with a structured learning plan and supervision, or (c) regular productive work akin to employment? Also confirm candidate age and nationality/visa status.
- (If applicable) Please confirm stipend amount, internship duration, weekly hours, and whether the company intends to treat the intern as a "trainee" or a "temporary employee."

---
Below is the original draft with inline bracketed legal suggestions. Preserve the original text and headings where possible; bracketed comments indicate suggested edits, required clarifying language, or optional stronger clauses. Where a full replacement clause is recommended, I provide the recommended wording inside the bracketed suggestion.

[Note to HR: Do not remove these bracketed comments until legal sign-off. Each bracketed comment identifies legal risk and recommends remedial language.]

[Document begins — original content preserved; bracketed comments inserted inline]

Date: [Insert Date]

