Additional Legal Notes & Recommendations (not inline)
- IP assignment enforceability under Indian law: Assignment of copyright/patent is enforceable if in writing and signed by assignor. For works created during an internship, a clear written assignment together with the consideration (stipend/training) and requirement to sign further documents (assignment deeds) strengthens enforceability. Keep explicit records of when works were created and under whose supervision.
- Confidentiality duration: A 3-year survival for confidentiality plus indefinite protection for trade secrets is reasonable. Courts may scrutinize overly broad confidentiality terms — ensure definitions are clear and limited to legitimate business interests.
- Stipend classification: Use "training stipend" language, clarify it's not salary, specify that intern is not entitled to employment benefits. However, if intern performs substantive productive work, PF/ESI and other benefits may be triggered. Maintain a clear training plan, supervised hours, and no guarantee of employment to help reduce misclassification risk.
- Apprentices Act & registration: If the internship is part of an academic course or designated as an apprenticeship, register under the Apprentices Act; failure to do so can lead to penalties. If unsure, HR should provide the learning plan and confirm whether the program maps to an accredited course.
- Tax/TDS: Company must deduct TDS if applicable. Interns may be required to submit PAN, and the Company should include TDS language and request PAN and bank details.
- Termination: Keep notice short (e.g., one week) or allow immediate termination for cause. Ensure pro rata stipend payment and return obligations are specified.

Requested clarifications for HR (repeat, concise)
- Is this internship (a) part of an academic course / apprenticeship, (b) purely voluntary training, or (c) performing core productive work for the Company?
- Intern's age and nationality/visa status.
- Stipend amount, expected weekly hours, and length of internship.

